 651:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** * \brief
 652:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *  Sets a new value for the specified parameter in the \ref group_structures.
 653:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *
 654:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** * \details
 655:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *  This function sets the value of the specified parameter by the paramId
 656:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *  argument. The paramId for each register is available in the
 657:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *  CapSense_1 RegisterMap header file as
 658:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *  CapSense_1_<ParameterName>_PARAM_ID. The paramId is a special
 659:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *  enumerated value generated by the customizer. The format of paramId is as
 660:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *  follows:
 661:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *    1. [ byte 3 byte 2 byte 1 byte 0 ]
 662:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *    2. [ TTWFCCCC UIIIIIII MMMMMMMM LLLLLLLL ]
 663:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *    3. T - encodes the parameter type:
 664:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *      - 01b: uint8
 665:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *      - 10b: uint16
 666:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *      - 11b: uint32
 667:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *    4. W - indicates whether the parameter is writable:
 668:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *      - 0: ReadOnly
 669:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *      - 1: Read/Write
 670:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *    5. C - 4 bit CRC (X^3 + 1) of the whole paramId word, the C bits are
 671:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *       filled with 0s when the CRC is calculated.
 672:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *    6. U - indicates if the parameter affects the RAM Widget Object CRC.
 673:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *    7. I - specifies that the widgetId parameter belongs to
 674:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *    8. M,L - the parameter offset MSB and LSB accordingly in:
 675:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *      - Flash Data Structure if W bit is 0.
 676:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *      - RAM Data Structure if W bit is 1.
 677:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *
 678:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *  Refer to the \ref group_structures section for details of the data structure
 679:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *  organization and examples of its register access.
 680:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *
 681:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *  This function writes specified value into the desired register without
 682:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *  other registers update. It is application layer responsibility to keep all
 683:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *  the data structure registers aligned. Repeated call of
 684:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *  CapSense_1_Start() function helps aligning dependent register values.
