 873:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *  detection status.
 874:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *  A macro for the sensor ID within the specified widget can be found in the
 875:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *  CapSense_1 Configuration header file defined as
 876:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *  CapSense_1_<WidgetName>_SNS<SensorNumber>_ID.
 877:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *
 878:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** * \return
 879:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *  Returns the touch detection status of the specified sensor / widget:
 880:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *    - Zero if no touch is detected in the specified sensor / widget or a wrong
 881:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *      widget ID / sensor ID is specified.
 882:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *    - Non-zero if the specified sensor is active i.e. touch is detected. If the
 883:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *      specific sensor belongs to a proximity widget, the proximity detection
 884:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_1_Structure.c **** *      status is returned.
